My understanding was that during the wormhole incident the underlying ETH backing ETH on Solana got drained

Yet Solana ETH could still be bridged to other chains / to Ethereum?

Unless I'm mistaken I follow VC chains from a safe distance, the ğŸ’© smell is strong

It's alright to bridge 2 quite safe chains together. Issues arise when you bridge an HQ chain like #Ethereum to a shit show like #BSC or #Solana

Many/all bridges emit IOUs + depend on a wallet/multisig with weak opsec to secure the underlying...

ğŸ”®Who knows how this ends?

Of course, all chains wanna bridge to #Ethereum for the value they draw from it.

Yet, with the current main model for bridge (IOU), the risks are NOT properly segregated as demonstrated with the Solana Worhmhole debacle

The more we connect the chains, the more we mutualize risk

There is a dirty little secret still quite unsaid about the multichain future:

Every new bridge increases the attack surface.

ğŸ The multichain hydra is as strong as the weakest chain it bridges to

=> Do we really wanna bridge #Ethereum to all chains, even weak ones?
